    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="753"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d753">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Loomis</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 17, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 249.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your No. 260, of the 26th ultimo, I
                    have to say that inquiry at the Navy Department reveals the fact that the fleet
                    under Rear-Admiral Sampson was expected to have reached La Guaira on the 8th
                    instant, but it is reported to have arrived there on the 5th instant. It is
                    understood it will remain for several days.</p>
                <p>Admiral Sampson’s instructions were, on arriving in Venezuelan waters, to place
                    himself in immediate telegraphic communication with you, and, through you, to
                    arrange for his presentation to the President of Venezuela. The Department
                    doubts not you have, ere <pb facs="0875" n="779" xml:id="pg_779"/> this, had the
                    pleasure of carrying out the wishes of the Secretary of the Navy in this
                    respect.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
